title: Driver
description: The ioLibrary means "Internet Offload Library" for WIZnet chip. It includes drivers and application protocols. There are three kinds of libraries explained on this page The first two drivers (ioLibrary\_BSD, ioLibrary) can be used for W5500 application designs. These will be updated continuously. The former BSD-Type driver will not be updated, as it is only meant to be a migration help from W5200 to W5500.
